        <title>List of all formats</title>
        <para>
            All formats which need to be self defined correspond to the ISO 8601 norm. However, not 
            all formats defined in the ISO norm are supported. Die format length is unlimited. Also 
            the multiple usage of formats is allowed.
        </para>
        <para>
            The following example illustrates the usage:
        </para>
        <example>
            <title>Example usage for self defined formats</title>
            <programlisting role="php"><![CDATA[<?php
require_once 'Zend.php';
Zend::loadClass('Zend_Date');

$locale = new Zend_Locale('de_AT');
$date = new Zend_Date(1234567890, false, $locale);
print $date->toString("'Era:GGGG='GGGG, ' Date:yy.MMMM.dd'yy.MMMM.dd");
?>]]></programlisting>
        </example>
